<%- include('partials/header') %>

<div class="landing">
  <div class="hero">
    <div class="hero-eyebrow"><span></span> Self-hosted · Open source · Free</div>
    <h1>Deploy Node.js apps<br>in seconds</h1>
    <p class="tagline">One-click deploy from GitHub. Process management, live monitoring, env variables, and AI diagnostics — all in one panel.</p>
    <div class="hero-buttons">
      <a href="/auth/register" class="btn btn-primary btn-lg">Get Started Free →</a>
      <a href="/auth/login" class="btn btn-secondary btn-lg">Sign In</a>
    </div>
    <div class="hero-stats">
      <div class="hero-stat"><strong>1-click</strong><span>Deploy</span></div>
      <div class="hero-stat"><strong>PM2</strong><span>Process Mgmt</span></div>
      <div class="hero-stat"><strong>AI</strong><span>Diagnostics</span></div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="features">
    <div class="feature-card">
      <div class="feature-icon">🚀</div>
      <h3>One-Click Deploy</h3>
      <p>Connect your Git repo and hit deploy. We handle npm install, PM2 process management, and auto-restart on crash.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="feature-card">
      <div class="feature-icon">📊</div>
      <h3>Live Monitoring</h3>
      <p>Real-time RAM, CPU usage, uptime tracking, and restart counts. Know exactly how every app is performing.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="feature-card">
      <div class="feature-icon">🤖</div>
      <h3>AI Assistant</h3>
      <p>Built-in AI that analyzes your logs, suggests env vars, debugs crashes, and recommends optimal resource limits. No API key needed.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="feature-card">
      <div class="feature-icon">⚙️</div>
      <h3>Env Variables</h3>
      <p>Manage all environment variables from the dashboard. AI auto-suggests the vars your app needs based on the repo.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="feature-card">
      <div class="feature-icon">🔄</div>
      <h3>Auto-Restart</h3>
      <p>Apps crash? They restart automatically. Memory limit exceeded? PM2 caps it and restarts cleanly every time.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="feature-card">
      <div class="feature-icon">🛡️</div>
      <h3>Admin Panel</h3>
      <p>Multi-user support with per-user resource limits. Full admin controls for user management and server oversight.</p>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>

